Bootstrap: localimage
From: ./ubuntu_22.04.sif

%post
    set -e
    export DEBIAN_FRONTEND=noninteractive

    # Update package lists and install required system packages
    apt-get update
    apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends \
        python3 \
        python3-pip \
        iputils-ping

    # Install pytest for the grader
    pip3 install --no-cache-dir pytest

    # Prepare the workspace expected by the tests / student
    mkdir -p /home/user
    # Grant broad permissions so the (non-root) runtime user can write here
    chmod 0777 /home/user

    # Clean up APT caches to keep the image lean
    apt-get clean
    rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*

%environment
    chmod 755 /home/user

    # Ensure Python and user-installed binaries are on the PATH
    export PATH="/usr/local/bin:/usr/bin:/bin:$PATH"
    export LC_ALL=C.UTF-8

%labels
    Author Student
    Description "Container for FinOps loop-back latency test – provides ping, Python, and pytest."

%help
    This Apptainer image supplies:
      • iputils-ping  – standard ICMP diagnostics tool
      • Python 3      – runtime for student scripts
      • pytest        – testing framework used by the automated grader

    The /home/user directory is pre-created and world-writable so that
    unprivileged users (as enforced by Apptainer) can generate required
    artefacts during grading.